TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed EfxEffectf extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: A list of valid 32-Bits Float Effect/GetEffect parameters

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf AutowahAttackTime = int32(1)
AutowahAttackTime = 1

Docs.summary: This property controls the time the filtering effect takes to sweep from minimum to maximum center frequency when it is triggered by input signal. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0001f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.06f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf AutowahPeakGain = int32(4)
AutowahPeakGain = 4

Docs.summary: This property controls the input signal level at which the band-pass filter will be fully opened. Range [0.00003f .. 31621.0f] Default: 11.22f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf AutowahReleaseTime = int32(2)
AutowahReleaseTime = 2

Docs.summary: This property controls the time the filtering effect takes to sweep from maximum back to base center frequency, when the input signal ends. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0001f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.06f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf AutowahResonance = int32(3)
AutowahResonance = 3

Docs.summary: This property controls the resonant peak, sometimes known as emphasis or Q, of the auto-wah band-pass filter. Range [2.0f .. 1000.0f] Default: 1000.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ChorusDelay = int32(6)
ChorusDelay = 6

Docs.summary: This property controls the average amount of time the sample is delayed before it is played back, and with feedback, the amount of time between iterations of the sample. Larger values lower the pitch. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.016f] Default: 0.016f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ChorusDepth = int32(4)
ChorusDepth = 4

Docs.summary: This property controls the amount by which the delay time is modulated by the low-frequency oscillator. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.1f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ChorusFeedback = int32(5)
ChorusFeedback = 5

Docs.summary: This property controls the amount of processed signal that is fed back to the input of the chorus effect. Negative values will reverse the phase of the feedback signal. At full magnitude the identical sample will repeat endlessly. Range [-1.0f .. +1.0f] Default: +0.25f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ChorusRate = int32(3)
ChorusRate = 3

Docs.summary: This property sets the modulation rate of the low-frequency oscillator that controls the delay time of the delayed signals. Unit: Hz Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 1.1f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf DistortionEdge = int32(1)
DistortionEdge = 1

Docs.summary: This property controls the shape of the distortion. The higher the value for Edge, the "dirtier" and "fuzzier" the effect. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.2f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf DistortionEQBandwidth = int32(5)
DistortionEQBandwidth = 5

Docs.summary: This property controls the bandwidth of the post-distortion attenuation. Unit: Hz Range [80.0f .. 24000.0f] Default: 3600.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf DistortionEQCenter = int32(4)
DistortionEQCenter = 4

Docs.summary: This property controls the frequency at which the post-distortion attenuation (Distortion Gain) is active. Unit: Hz Range [80.0f .. 24000.0f] Default: 3600.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf DistortionGain = int32(2)
DistortionGain = 2

Docs.summary: This property allows you to attenuate the distorted sound. Range [0.01f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.05f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf DistortionLowpassCutoff = int32(3)
DistortionLowpassCutoff = 3

Docs.summary: Input signals can have a low pass filter applied, to limit the amount of high frequency signal feeding into the distortion effect. Unit: Hz Range [80.0f .. 24000.0f] Default: 8000.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbAirAbsorptionGainHF = int32(19)
EaxReverbAirAbsorptionGainHF = 19

Docs.summary: The Air Absorption Gain HF property controls the distance-dependent attenuation at high frequencies caused by the propagation medium. It applies to reflected sound only. Range [0.892f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.994f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbDecayHFRatio = int32(7)
EaxReverbDecayHFRatio = 7

Docs.summary: Decay HF Ratio scales the decay time of high frequencies relative to the value of the Decay Time property. By changing this value, you are changing the amount of time it takes for the high frequencies to decay compared to the mid frequencies of the reverb. Range [0.1f .. 2.0f] Default: 0.83f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbDecayLFRatio = int32(8)
EaxReverbDecayLFRatio = 8

Docs.summary: Decay LF Ratio scales the decay time of low frequencies in the reverberation in the same manner that Decay HF Ratio handles high frequencies. Unit: Linear multiplier Range [0.1f .. 2.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbDecayTime = int32(6)
EaxReverbDecayTime = 6

Docs.summary: The Decay Time property sets the reverberation decay time. It ranges from 0.1f (typically a small room with very dead surfaces) to 20.0f (typically a large room with very live surfaces). Unit: Seconds Range [0.1f .. 20.0f] Default: 1.49f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbDensity = int32(1)
EaxReverbDensity = 1

Docs.summary: Reverb Modal Density controls the coloration of the late reverb. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbDiffusion = int32(2)
EaxReverbDiffusion = 2

Docs.summary: The Reverb Diffusion property controls the echo density in the reverberation decay. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbEchoDepth = int32(16)
EaxReverbEchoDepth = 16

Docs.summary: Echo Depth introduces a cyclic echo in the reverberation decay, which will be noticeable with transient or percussive sounds. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbEchoTime = int32(15)
EaxReverbEchoTime = 15

Docs.summary: Echo Time controls the rate at which the cyclic echo repeats itself along the reverberation decay. Range [0.075f .. 0.25f] Default: 0.25f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbGain = int32(3)
EaxReverbGain = 3

Docs.summary: Reverb Gain controls the level of the reverberant sound in an environment. A high level of reverb is characteristic of rooms with highly reflective walls and/or small dimensions. Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.32f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbGainHF = int32(4)
EaxReverbGainHF = 4

Docs.summary: Gain HF is used to attenuate the high frequency content of all the reflected sound in an environment. You can use this property to give a room specific spectral characteristic. Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.89f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbGainLF = int32(5)
EaxReverbGainLF = 5

Docs.summary: Gain LF is the low frequency counterpart to Gain HF. Use this to reduce or boost the low frequency content in an environment. Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbHFReference = int32(20)
EaxReverbHFReference = 20

Docs.summary: The property HF reference determines the frequency at which the high-frequency effects created by Reverb properties are measured. Unit: Hz Range [1000.0f .. 20000.0f] Default: 5000.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbLateReverbDelay = int32(13)
EaxReverbLateReverbDelay = 13

Docs.summary: The Late Reverb Delay property defines the begin time of the late reverberation relative to the time of the initial reflection (the first of the early reflections). It ranges from 0 to 100 milliseconds. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.1f] Default: 0.011f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbLateReverbGain = int32(12)
EaxReverbLateReverbGain = 12

Docs.summary: The Late Reverb Gain property controls the overall amount of later reverberation relative to the Gain property. Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 1.26f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbLFReference = int32(21)
EaxReverbLFReference = 21

Docs.summary: The property LF reference determines the frequency at which the low-frequency effects created by Reverb properties are measured. Unit: Hz Range [20.0f .. 1000.0f] Default: 250.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbModulationDepth = int32(18)
EaxReverbModulationDepth = 18

Docs.summary: Modulation Depth controls the amount of pitch change. Low values of Diffusion will contribute to reinforcing the perceived effect by reducing the mixing of overlapping reflections in the reverberation decay. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbModulationTime = int32(17)
EaxReverbModulationTime = 17

Docs.summary: Modulation Time controls the speed of the rate of periodic changes in pitch (vibrato). Range [0.04f .. 4.0f] Default: 0.25f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbReflectionsDelay = int32(10)
EaxReverbReflectionsDelay = 10

Docs.summary: Reflections Delay controls the amount of time it takes for the first reflected wave front to reach the listener, relative to the arrival of the direct-path sound. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.3f] Default: 0.007f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbReflectionsGain = int32(9)
EaxReverbReflectionsGain = 9

Docs.summary: Reflections Gain sets the level of the early reflections in an environment. Early reflections are used as a cue for determining the size of the environment we are in. Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 3.16f] Default: 0.05f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EaxReverbRoomRolloffFactor = int32(22)
EaxReverbRoomRolloffFactor = 22

Docs.summary: The Room Rolloff Factor property is one of two methods available to attenuate the reflected sound (containing both reflections and reverberation) according to source-listener distance. It's defined the same way as OpenAL Rolloff Factor, but operates on reverb sound instead of direct-path sound. Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 0.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EchoDamping = int32(3)
EchoDamping = 3

Docs.summary: This property controls the amount of high frequency damping applied to each echo. As the sound is subsequently fed back for further echoes, damping results in an echo which progressively gets softer in tone as well as intensity. Range [0.0f .. 0.99f] Default: 0.5f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EchoDelay = int32(1)
EchoDelay = 1

Docs.summary: This property controls the delay between the original sound and the first "tap", or echo instance. Subsequently, the value for Echo Delay is used to determine the time delay between each "second tap" and the next "first tap". Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.207f] Default: 0.1f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EchoFeedback = int32(4)
EchoFeedback = 4

Docs.summary: This property controls the amount of feedback the output signal fed back into the input. Use this parameter to create "cascading" echoes. At full magnitude, the identical sample will repeat endlessly. Below full magnitude, the sample will repeat and fade. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.5f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EchoLRDelay = int32(2)
EchoLRDelay = 2

Docs.summary: This property controls the delay between the "first tap" and the "second tap". Subsequently, the value for Echo LR Delay is used to determine the time delay between each "first tap" and the next "second tap". Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.404f] Default: 0.1f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EchoSpread = int32(5)
EchoSpread = 5

Docs.summary: This property controls how hard panned the individual echoes are. With a value of 1.0f, the first "tap" will be panned hard left, and the second "tap" hard right. –1.0f gives the opposite result and values near to 0.0f result in less emphasized panning. Range [-1.0f .. +1.0f] Default: -1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerHighCutoff = int32(10)
EqualizerHighCutoff = 10

Docs.summary: This property controls the high frequency above which signal will be cut off. Unit: Hz Range [4000.0f .. 16000.0f] Default: 6000.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerHighGain = int32(9)
EqualizerHighGain = 9

Docs.summary: This property allows to cut/boost the signal at high frequencies. Range [0.126f .. 7.943f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerLowCutoff = int32(2)
EqualizerLowCutoff = 2

Docs.summary: This property controls the low frequency below which signal will be cut off. Unit: Hz Range [50.0f .. 800.0f] Default: 200.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerLowGain = int32(1)
EqualizerLowGain = 1

Docs.summary: This property controls amount of cut or boost on the low frequency range. Range [0.126f .. 7.943f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid1Center = int32(4)
EqualizerMid1Center = 4

Docs.summary: This property sets the center frequency for the "mid1" range. Unit: Hz Range [200.0f .. 3000.0f] Default: 500.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid1Gain = int32(3)
EqualizerMid1Gain = 3

Docs.summary: This property allows you to cut/boost signal on the "mid1" range. Range [0.126f .. 7.943f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid1Width = int32(5)
EqualizerMid1Width = 5

Docs.summary: This property controls the width of the "mid1" range. Range [0.01f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid2Center = int32(7)
EqualizerMid2Center = 7

Docs.summary: This property sets the center frequency for the "mid2" range. Unit: Hz Range [1000.0f .. 8000.0f] Default: 3000.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid2Gain = int32(6)
EqualizerMid2Gain = 6

Docs.summary: This property allows you to cut/boost signal on the "mid2" range. Range [0.126f .. 7.943f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf EqualizerMid2Width = int32(8)
EqualizerMid2Width = 8

Docs.summary: This property controls the width of the "mid2" range. Range [0.01f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf FlangerDelay = int32(6)
FlangerDelay = 6

Docs.summary: The average amount of time the sample is delayed before it is played back. When used with the Feedback property it's the amount of time between iterations of the sample. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.004f] Default: 0.002f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf FlangerDepth = int32(4)
FlangerDepth = 4

Docs.summary: The ratio by which the delay time is modulated by the low-frequency oscillator. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf FlangerFeedback = int32(5)
FlangerFeedback = 5

Docs.summary: This is the amount of the output signal level fed back into the effect's input. A negative value will reverse the phase of the feedback signal. Range [-1.0f .. +1.0f] Default: -0.5f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf FlangerRate = int32(3)
FlangerRate = 3

Docs.summary: The number of times per second the low-frequency oscillator controlling the amount of delay repeats. Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 0.27f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf FrequencyShifterFrequency = int32(1)
FrequencyShifterFrequency = 1

Docs.summary: This is the carrier frequency. For carrier frequencies below the audible range, the single sideband modulator may produce phaser effects, spatial effects or a slight pitch-shift. As the carrier frequency increases, the timbre of the sound is affected. Unit: Hz Range [0.0f .. 24000.0f] Default: 0.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbAirAbsorptionGainHF = int32(11)
ReverbAirAbsorptionGainHF = 11

Docs.summary: The Air Absorption Gain HF property controls the distance-dependent attenuation at high frequencies caused by the propagation medium and applies to reflected sound only. Unit: Linear gain per meter Range [0.892f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.994f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbDecayHFRatio = int32(6)
ReverbDecayHFRatio = 6

Docs.summary: The Decay HF Ratio property sets the spectral quality of the Decay Time parameter. It is the ratio of high-frequency decay time relative to the time set by Decay Time.. Unit: linear multiplier Range [0.1f .. 2.0f] Default: 0.83f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbDecayTime = int32(5)
ReverbDecayTime = 5

Docs.summary: The Decay Time property sets the reverberation decay time. It ranges from 0.1f (typically a small room with very dead surfaces) to 20.0 (typically a large room with very live surfaces). Unit: Seconds Range [0.1f .. 20.0f] Default: 1.49f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbDensity = int32(1)
ReverbDensity = 1

Docs.summary: Reverb Modal Density controls the coloration of the late reverb. Lowering the value adds more coloration to the late reverb. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbDiffusion = int32(2)
ReverbDiffusion = 2

Docs.summary: The Reverb Diffusion property controls the echo density in the reverberation decay. The default 1.0f provides the highest density. Reducing diffusion gives the reverberation a more "grainy" character that is especially noticeable with percussive sound sources. If you set a diffusion value of 0.0f, the later reverberation sounds like a succession of distinct echoes. Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 1.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbGain = int32(3)
ReverbGain = 3

Docs.summary: The Reverb Gain property is the master volume control for the reflected sound - both early reflections and reverberation - that the reverb effect adds to all sound sources. Ranges from 1.0 (0db) (the maximum amount) to 0.0 (-100db) (no reflected sound at all) are accepted. Units: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.32f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbGainHF = int32(4)
ReverbGainHF = 4

Docs.summary: The Reverb Gain HF property further tweaks reflected sound by attenuating it at high frequencies. It controls a low-pass filter that applies globally to the reflected sound of all sound sources feeding the particular instance of the reverb effect. Ranges from 1.0f (0db) (no filter) to 0.0f (-100db) (virtually no reflected sound) are accepted. Units: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 1.0f] Default: 0.89f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbLateReverbDelay = int32(10)
ReverbLateReverbDelay = 10

Docs.summary: The Late Reverb Delay property defines the begin time of the late reverberation relative to the time of the initial reflection (the first of the early reflections). It ranges from 0 to 100 milliseconds. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.1f] Default: 0.011f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbLateReverbGain = int32(9)
ReverbLateReverbGain = 9

Docs.summary: The Late Reverb Gain property controls the overall amount of later reverberation relative to the Gain property. The value of Late Reverb Gain ranges from a maximum of 10.0f (+20 dB) to a minimum of 0.0f (-100 dB) (no late reverberation at all). Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 1.26f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbReflectionsDelay = int32(8)
ReverbReflectionsDelay = 8

Docs.summary: The Reflections Delay property is the amount of delay between the arrival time of the direct path from the source to the first reflection from the source. It ranges from 0 to 300 milliseconds. Unit: Seconds Range [0.0f .. 0.3f] Default: 0.007f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbReflectionsGain = int32(7)
ReverbReflectionsGain = 7

Docs.summary: The Reflections Gain property controls the overall amount of initial reflections relative to the Gain property. The value of Reflections Gain ranges from a maximum of 3.16f (+10 dB) to a minimum of 0.0f (-100 dB) (no initial reflections at all), and is corrected by the value of the Gain property. Unit: Linear gain Range [0.0f .. 3.16f] Default: 0.05f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf ReverbRoomRolloffFactor = int32(12)
ReverbRoomRolloffFactor = 12

Docs.summary: The Room Rolloff Factor property is one of two methods available to attenuate the reflected sound (containing both reflections and reverberation) according to source-listener distance. It's defined the same way as OpenAL's Rolloff Factor, but operates on reverb sound instead of direct-path sound. Unit: Linear multiplier Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 0.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf RingModulatorFrequency = int32(1)
RingModulatorFrequency = 1

Docs.summary: This is the frequency of the carrier signal. If the carrier signal is slowly varying (less than 20 Hz), the result is a slow amplitude variation effect (tremolo). Unit: Hz Range [0.0f .. 8000.0f] Default: 440.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf RingModulatorHighpassCutoff = int32(2)
RingModulatorHighpassCutoff = 2

Docs.summary: This controls the cutoff frequency at which the input signal is high-pass filtered before being ring modulated. Unit: Hz Range [0.0f .. 24000.0f] Default: 800.0f

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype OpenTK.Audio.OpenAL.EfxEffectf VocalMorpherRate = int32(6)
VocalMorpherRate = 6

Docs.summary: This controls the frequency of the low-frequency oscillator used to morph between the two phoneme filters. Unit: Hz Range [0.0f .. 10.0f] Default: 1.41f
